# Claude OKF Adapter

Use `.okf` as the shared project context layer.

Read `.okf/index.md`, `.okf/project.md`, relevant concepts, recent handoffs, and applicable `.okf/improvements/` lessons before project changes.

Prefer reviewed, tested, and accepted OKF concepts over draft or unverified material. Preserve citations and external references when updating concepts.

After substantive changes, update OKF and append to `.okf/log.md`. Create a handoff before stopping if another agent may need to continue.
